Class DREFramework

java.lang.Object
  edu.ncsu.dre.DREFramework

public class DREFramework
extends java.lang.Object

This is the application's main interface point to the DRE Framework.

This class provides the basic methods and constructors for building the application.

Constructor Detail

DREFramework

public DREFramework()
Constructor for the DREFramework, users will have to explicitly use either of the setConfiguration method to define the components of the framework. Else a DREIllegalStateException will be thrown. The hasValidConfiguration() method can be used to check if a valid configuration has been set for this instance. Extensions to this class can enforce a default configuration if necessary.

processArtifact

public void processArtifact(Artifact inputArtifact)
This method initiates the research operation. First the artifact is passed through the Segregator component (as per configuration) where it is divided into sub queries. The sub queries are given to the Scheduler component which then schedules the processing onto different service providers. Once all service providers have responded, the scheduler passes the results to Aggregator which collates the result set.

Parameters:
inputArtifact -

hasValidConfiguration

public boolean hasValidConfiguration()
This method checks to see if the framework has been set with a valid configuration. True if this instance of framework has a valid Segregator, Aggregator and a scheduler

Returns:
boolean
